DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "parserFormulaUpToConstant.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->are(t=>["Real", limits=>[0.15,0.75]]);

$r = random(2,4,1);
$r1 = $r+1;
$p = random(2,4,1);
$p1 = $p+1;
$a = random(1,6,1);

$func = Compute("t^{$r} (t^{$r1} - $a)^{$p}");
$afunc = FormulaUpToConstant("(t^($r1) - $a)^($p1)/($p1*$r1) + C");

Context("Numeric");

TEXT(beginproblem());
Context()->texStrings;
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Find the following integral.  Note that you can check your answer by
differentiation.

$PAR
\( \displaystyle \int\, $func \,dt = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS($afunc->cmp() );

$rp1 = $r1*$p1;

Context()->texStrings;
Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

We use substitution with \(w = t^{$r1} - $a\).  Then 
\(dw = $r1 t^{$r}\,dt\), so that 
\[
  \int\,t^{$r} (t^{$r1} - $a)^{$p}\,dt = 
  {1\over $r1}\int\,w^{$p}\,dw = {1\over $rp1} w^{$p1} + C = 
  {1\over $rp1} (t^{$r1} - $a)^{$p1} + C.
\]

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;
Context()->normalStrings;


;
